WEBVTT

00:01.540 --> 00:04.290
♪♪

00:04.290 --> 00:05.420
What are you making?

00:05.420 --> 00:06.830
Mashed cauliflower
for my mom.

00:06.830 --> 00:08.080
She has dietary
restrictions.

00:08.080 --> 00:10.420
Yes, I know.
She has an angry bowel.

00:10.420 --> 00:11.750
It's irritable.

00:11.750 --> 00:13.880
Like your parents coming
for Thanksgiving makes me.

00:13.880 --> 00:15.460
For the next six hours,
I need you to be

00:15.460 --> 00:16.880
courteous, kind,
and respectful.

00:16.880 --> 00:18.000
That's not fair.

00:18.000 --> 00:21.170
That's like me asking you
to catch a football.

00:21.170 --> 00:24.330
Sportscaster: ...Jackson --
a perfectly thrown ball --

00:24.330 --> 00:26.620
Hey! I was just about
to look up at that.

00:26.620 --> 00:27.830
[ Blows ]

00:27.830 --> 00:29.250
What are you doing?

00:29.250 --> 00:30.750
Making it look
dusty and unused.

00:30.750 --> 00:32.210
My parents are coming,
and I was raised --

00:32.210 --> 00:34.250
Without a TV.

00:34.250 --> 00:36.460
Just because you grew up with
the worst life imaginable --

00:36.460 --> 00:37.540
I had books.

00:37.540 --> 00:39.170
We're saying
the same thing --

00:39.170 --> 00:41.710
doesn't mean we should suffer
every time they visit.

00:41.710 --> 00:43.380
I don't want my dad to think
we're slaves to technology.

00:43.380 --> 00:44.580
[ Cellphone chimes ]

00:44.580 --> 00:46.210
Oh, my God.

00:47.670 --> 00:48.500
Hey, give it back!

00:48.500 --> 00:49.580
Not happening.

00:49.580 --> 00:51.790
Dad, we all just watched
that show

00:51.790 --> 00:53.080
about
the Menendez Brothers.

00:53.080 --> 00:54.710
Let's think about this.

00:54.710 --> 00:56.790
You'll get them back
when my parents have left.

00:56.790 --> 00:58.960
Until then, why not communicate
the old-fashioned way --

00:58.960 --> 01:00.880
using words and eye contact.

01:00.880 --> 01:03.750
Red-faced angry emoji.

01:07.210 --> 01:08.710
Guess who's ready
for the holidays.

01:08.710 --> 01:10.170
[ Snorting ]

01:10.170 --> 01:11.960
Hans Gruber can't be here
right now.

01:11.960 --> 01:14.080
[ Snorts]
Why?

01:14.080 --> 01:16.380
Because my dad can't find out
we have a pet pig.
Why?

01:16.380 --> 01:18.000
Because he wouldn't
approve.
Why?

01:18.000 --> 01:19.830
Because Grandpa doesn't
like cute things.

01:19.830 --> 01:21.380
Why?
Because I'm cute,

01:21.380 --> 01:22.750
and he didn't approve
when Daddy married me.

01:22.750 --> 01:23.540
That's not true.

01:23.540 --> 01:24.620
Why?

01:24.620 --> 01:25.960
Because I was
beneath Daddy.

01:25.960 --> 01:27.290
You mean like the time

01:27.290 --> 01:28.170
I opened your door
without knocking?

01:29.920 --> 01:32.750
You, take Hans Gruber upstairs
and hide him in your room.

01:32.750 --> 01:35.120
And you, take your hair
out of that ponytail

01:35.120 --> 01:36.250
and make it look
more festive.

01:36.250 --> 01:37.580
Want to give me
styling tips?

01:37.580 --> 01:39.040
Yes, use a curling iron
to give it a light bounce.

01:40.960 --> 01:43.040
And you -- Actually,
you're dressed appropriately

01:43.040 --> 01:44.500
and you're involved in ballet,
something cultural.

01:44.500 --> 01:45.500
I have no notes for you.

01:45.500 --> 01:46.710
I'm the man.

01:46.710 --> 01:47.920
Actually, I do have
a note for you.

01:47.920 --> 01:49.750
Be 30% less Oliver.

01:51.960 --> 01:54.540
You get so uptight
when your parents visit.

01:54.540 --> 01:56.750
And you get uptight when
it's your mom's year to
come for Thanksgiving.

01:56.750 --> 01:59.420
That's because she's crazy,
and that makes me crazy.

01:59.420 --> 02:01.750
But you don't see me
turning myself inside out

02:01.750 --> 02:02.960
trying to please her.

02:02.960 --> 02:04.670
No, you just yell at her
in front of company

02:04.670 --> 02:05.750
and make everyone
uncomfortable.

02:05.750 --> 02:08.580
I do that. Yeah.

02:08.580 --> 02:09.580
It's different for me.

02:09.580 --> 02:10.710
You have brothers
and sisters.

02:10.710 --> 02:11.830
I'm an only child.

02:11.830 --> 02:13.960
All the attention
falls on me.

02:13.960 --> 02:15.500
I have to make him proud.

02:15.500 --> 02:16.960
When are you going
to stop trying

02:16.960 --> 02:18.250
to get your dad's approval?

02:18.250 --> 02:20.790
Right after this visit,
when I finally get it.

02:20.790 --> 02:22.380
I sent him an early copy
of my book --

02:22.380 --> 02:23.620
"John Stuart Mill
and the Consequences

02:23.620 --> 02:25.540
of a Thoroughgoing
Empiricist Outlook."

02:25.540 --> 02:27.880
JSM is his favorite
utilitarian philosopher.

02:27.880 --> 02:31.120
Did you trade JSM's rookie card
for a...

02:33.290 --> 02:36.040
If I knew another philosopher,
I would've totally landed that.

02:36.040 --> 02:38.040
I just need you
to get on board.

02:38.040 --> 02:39.540
Fine.

02:39.540 --> 02:41.210
But afterwards,
you're gonna owe me.

02:41.210 --> 02:43.460
I want you do that special thing
you know I like.

02:43.460 --> 02:44.830
Tell the kids
you're out for the night

02:44.830 --> 02:46.380
when, really,
you're just locked in our room

02:46.380 --> 02:47.620
with a coffee cup full
of chocolate chips,

02:47.620 --> 02:49.120
watching
"Beachfront Bargain Hunt?"

02:49.120 --> 02:50.920
Sounds so hot
when you say it.

02:50.920 --> 02:51.920
♪♪

02:57.670 --> 03:02.620
♪♪

03:02.620 --> 03:04.170
Busted.

03:04.170 --> 03:05.250
[ Sighs ]

03:05.250 --> 03:06.880
I need to get my phone back,

03:06.880 --> 03:09.120
but I can't figure out
the combination on the lock.

03:09.120 --> 03:11.000
Why do you need your phone
so bad?

03:11.000 --> 03:13.000
Eyo texted, "I love you."

03:13.000 --> 03:13.880
And...?

03:13.880 --> 03:15.460
He said, "I love you,"

03:15.460 --> 03:17.170
and that's the first time
he's ever said that.

03:17.170 --> 03:18.080
And before I could
text him back,

03:18.080 --> 03:19.290
Dad took my phone away.

03:19.290 --> 03:20.750
Wow.

03:20.750 --> 03:22.750
He's got to be thinking
you're totally icing him out.

03:22.750 --> 03:23.580
I know!

03:23.580 --> 03:24.920
Okay, listen.

03:24.920 --> 03:26.460
The sooner
Grandma and Grandpa leave,

03:26.460 --> 03:27.920
the sooner you'll get
your phone back.

03:27.920 --> 03:29.290
Right.

03:29.290 --> 03:31.750
This Thanksgiving has
to move fast.

03:31.750 --> 03:34.330
Wait.

03:34.330 --> 03:36.000
Ugh!

03:36.000 --> 03:38.500
I thought it might be Mom's
two favorite "Bachelor" seasons.

03:38.500 --> 03:40.330
13, 21.

03:40.330 --> 03:43.670
♪♪

03:43.670 --> 03:45.330
Oh, I love that outfit.

03:45.330 --> 03:46.380
This one?

03:46.380 --> 03:47.620
The one you laid out
on the bed for me

03:47.620 --> 03:49.170
with a note that says,
"Please wear it.

03:49.170 --> 03:50.330
My mommy and daddy
are coming?"

03:50.330 --> 03:51.830
You added that last part.

03:51.830 --> 03:53.380
You promised me
you'd be on board.

03:53.380 --> 03:55.380
Fine! I'm on board.

03:55.380 --> 03:56.460
But parents or no parents,

03:56.460 --> 03:58.120
this button is
getting unbuttoned

03:58.120 --> 03:59.750
20 minutes after
pumpkin pie.

03:59.750 --> 04:01.670
Unh-unh. Unh-unh.

04:01.670 --> 04:03.210
My parents are almost here,
and I said no electronics.

04:03.210 --> 04:05.170
This is an assignment
for school.

04:05.170 --> 04:07.750
I have to do a short film about
my family's Thanksgiving.

04:07.750 --> 04:09.920
Okay, but when
you use your camera

04:09.920 --> 04:11.040
around Grandma and Grandpa,

04:11.040 --> 04:12.920
make sure you call it
a "documentary."

04:12.920 --> 04:13.620
[ Doorbell rings ]

04:13.620 --> 04:14.920
They're here.

04:14.920 --> 04:16.620
They're here!
They're here!

04:16.620 --> 04:20.000
Everyone, look good.
Have a mint.

04:20.000 --> 04:21.790
[ Gasps ]
-Oh!

04:21.790 --> 04:23.540
There's no time to pick them up.
Just kick them in the vent!

04:28.000 --> 04:28.710
Spencer?

04:28.710 --> 04:29.750
Spencer?

04:29.750 --> 04:31.750
Happy Thanksgiving.

04:31.750 --> 04:33.120
You invited an ex-con
to our Thanksgiving?

04:33.120 --> 04:34.420
Yeah, he's all alone,

04:34.420 --> 04:36.000
and I wanted him to feel
like family --

04:36.000 --> 04:38.460
family you leave money to.

04:38.460 --> 04:39.750
What kind of person
befriends someone

04:39.750 --> 04:40.920
just to get
in their will?

04:40.920 --> 04:42.330
The kind who might not
take care of his father

04:42.330 --> 04:43.460
if he keeps up
the judgment.

04:44.540 --> 04:46.250
This is for you --

04:46.250 --> 04:48.710
a rare Bordeaux
I bought at auction.

04:48.710 --> 04:50.000
Do you have a decanter?

04:50.000 --> 04:52.500
I have a sun-tea jar.

04:52.500 --> 04:55.580
That's what they call decanters
in Florida.

04:55.580 --> 04:56.960
[ Beeping ]
I hear beeping.
Who's holding?

04:56.960 --> 04:58.580
Taylor.
It's not me.

04:58.580 --> 04:59.710
Oops. Sorry.

04:59.710 --> 05:01.710
I -- I guess
if I go past there,

05:01.710 --> 05:04.120
my ankle monitor's out of range
of my house.

05:05.210 --> 05:06.620
[ Beeping stops ]

05:06.620 --> 05:08.120
I don't want
my parole officer

05:08.120 --> 05:10.420
busting up
your Thanksgiving party.

05:10.420 --> 05:13.330
Pearl's fun at first,
but she wears on you.

05:13.330 --> 05:15.500
So sorry you can't stay.
Nonsense.

05:15.500 --> 05:17.170
I'll go get the card table
and set it up right here.

05:17.170 --> 05:18.750
[ Doorbell rings ]
It's them.

05:18.750 --> 05:20.120
Anna-Kat, stop eating mints
off the floor!

05:20.120 --> 05:21.460
I'll get it.
No, that's okay.

05:22.960 --> 05:25.040
Ah, happy Thanksgiving.

05:25.040 --> 05:26.620
[ Chuckles ]
Spencer Blitz.

05:26.620 --> 05:29.420
You're that investment banker
that they locked up.

05:29.420 --> 05:30.580
That's me.

05:30.580 --> 05:31.920
And now
I'm your son's doorman

05:31.920 --> 05:34.250
who's never allowed to play
the market again.

05:34.250 --> 05:36.380
[ Hushed ] Empire Energy's
about to make a run.

05:36.380 --> 05:38.710
[ Normal voice ]
May I take your coat?

05:38.710 --> 05:40.460
Oh!
Hi, honey!

05:40.460 --> 05:42.080
Hi, Mom.

05:42.080 --> 05:43.580
Hi, Dad.

05:43.580 --> 05:45.830
Any other criminal friends
coming for dinner?

05:45.830 --> 05:47.210
Oh, no. [ Chuckles ]

05:47.210 --> 05:49.170
Spencer's not my friend.
He's Oliver's friend.

05:49.170 --> 05:51.250
Oh, a boy and his felon.

05:51.250 --> 05:52.620
Warms the heart.

05:52.620 --> 05:54.460
Happy Thanksgiving!

05:54.460 --> 05:56.170
Katie!

05:56.170 --> 05:58.830
There is the woman that my son
insisted on marrying.

05:58.830 --> 06:01.880
[ Chuckles ] You.

06:01.880 --> 06:03.380
Anna-Kat:
Grandma, grandpa!

06:03.380 --> 06:04.580
Oh!

06:07.000 --> 06:08.710
[ Quietly ] Thank you.
That was perfectly handled.

06:08.710 --> 06:09.920
My secret is, I make a fist

06:09.920 --> 06:11.250
and dig my fingernails
into my hand.

06:11.250 --> 06:12.500
See?

06:12.500 --> 06:13.750
[ Normal voice ]
Is that blood?

06:13.750 --> 06:15.960
Yeah.

06:15.960 --> 06:17.540
All right, everyone's here!

06:17.540 --> 06:18.960
Let's all go
to the dinner table.

06:18.960 --> 06:21.540
The turkey still has
two more hours to cook.

06:21.540 --> 06:23.960
I say screw the turkey
and let's get on with it!

06:23.960 --> 06:25.210
[ Laughs nervously ]

06:26.500 --> 06:28.380
Nice try speeding up
Thanksgiving.

06:28.380 --> 06:31.380
Wait, what's that sound?

06:31.380 --> 06:33.040
It's Eyo weeping
as he checks his phone

06:33.040 --> 06:34.750
for a text
that never comes.

06:34.750 --> 06:37.750
♪♪

06:37.750 --> 06:39.120
Sorry about the card table,

06:39.120 --> 06:40.920
but it must be better
than your last Thanksgiving

06:40.920 --> 06:42.210
in federal prison.

06:42.210 --> 06:44.670
Oh, Guy Fieri was
our guest chef.

06:44.670 --> 06:46.580
Too spicy. Terrible!

06:46.580 --> 06:48.460
I've got sweatshirts
for everyone

06:48.460 --> 06:49.880
from Oxford University!

06:49.880 --> 06:51.880
He teaches there
in the summers.

06:51.880 --> 06:53.620
It's very prestigious.

06:53.620 --> 06:56.880
Yes, my job is prestigious,
but, um...

06:56.880 --> 06:59.580
it's not the only thing that
I'm proud of in my life.

06:59.580 --> 07:01.040
Greg?

07:01.040 --> 07:03.120
[ Sentimental music plays ]

07:03.120 --> 07:06.040
Tell 'em about the time that
I smoked Tony Blair at Scrabble.

07:06.040 --> 07:07.380
You just did, Dad.

07:07.380 --> 07:09.620
Katie: Greg is
impressive, too.

07:09.620 --> 07:11.500
You should see
the velvet-y professor thing

07:11.500 --> 07:14.330
he gets to wear around his neck
at every graduation ceremony.

07:14.330 --> 07:16.210
It's like he teaches
at Hogwarts!

07:16.210 --> 07:17.710
I'm good, honey.
Thank you.

07:17.710 --> 07:19.120
[ Doorbell rings ]

07:19.120 --> 07:20.500
I'll get it.

07:20.500 --> 07:23.120
Who is that?
We're not expecting anyone else.

07:23.120 --> 07:25.250
Well, hello!

07:25.250 --> 07:27.120
Hello, everyone.

07:27.120 --> 07:28.670
Mom?!

07:28.670 --> 07:30.790
[ Hushed ] You didn't tell me
the stiffs were coming.

07:30.790 --> 07:32.210
[ Hushed ]
I didn't tell you

07:32.210 --> 07:33.210
because you're not supposed
to be here.

07:33.210 --> 07:34.670
You're supposed to be
at Steph's.

07:34.670 --> 07:36.500
Well, your sister got caught up
in that travel ban,

07:36.500 --> 07:38.120
and now she's stuck
in Turkey.

07:38.120 --> 07:40.880
And it didn't occur to you
to call or give me a heads-up?

07:40.880 --> 07:42.750
What, so that you could come up
with some dumb excuse

07:42.750 --> 07:43.710
for why I couldn't come?

07:43.710 --> 07:44.790
Absolutely not.

07:44.790 --> 07:46.540
I can still make
an excuse.

07:46.540 --> 07:48.750
Oven's broken.
House is being fumigated.

07:48.750 --> 07:51.620
Uh...stay away from me.
You drive me [bleep] crazy.

07:51.620 --> 07:53.420
You know, I haven't been here
for 20 seconds,

07:53.420 --> 07:55.290
and you are already
on my ass.

07:55.290 --> 07:57.710
Lucky for you
I'm in a good mood.

07:57.710 --> 07:59.170
I had two road pinots.

08:00.540 --> 08:02.120
Katie, can I talk to you
for a minute?

08:03.500 --> 08:04.500
In private?

08:07.620 --> 08:09.540
Do you know how to make
a whiskey sour?

08:09.540 --> 08:12.000
♪♪

08:12.000 --> 08:13.830
I can't believe your mom
crashed Thanksgiving.

08:13.830 --> 08:15.000
She doesn't even
think to call!

08:15.000 --> 08:16.750
It's bad enough we have
an ex-con in the house.

08:16.750 --> 08:18.500
Now we'll have your
soon-to-be-tipsy mom

08:18.500 --> 08:20.210
telling my parents
dumb stewardess stories

08:20.210 --> 08:22.330
about how she had a layover
with James Caan.

08:22.330 --> 08:23.540
She always stresses
the "lay."

08:23.540 --> 08:25.920
You're saying that as though
old Snooty and Tooty

08:25.920 --> 08:26.830
are too good for my mother.

08:26.830 --> 08:28.250
Oh, come on, Katie.

08:28.250 --> 08:30.330
My dad is a three-time
National Dickens Scholar.

08:30.330 --> 08:33.830
James Caan was
in "The Godfather I" and "II."

08:33.830 --> 08:34.790
What's your point?

08:34.790 --> 08:36.290
My point is that
I would listen

08:36.290 --> 08:37.750
to my mom's stories
till the end of time

08:37.750 --> 08:39.920
if it meant never having to hear
your father go on

08:39.920 --> 08:40.960
about his favorite author.

08:40.960 --> 08:42.540
What's his name again?
Scrotum?

08:42.540 --> 08:43.420
Balzac.

08:43.420 --> 08:44.420
I knew I was close.

08:44.420 --> 08:46.830
My parent is
a world-famous scholar.

08:46.830 --> 08:48.580
Yours is
a world-traveling tramp.

08:48.580 --> 08:50.710
That's it!
I'm off board!

08:50.710 --> 08:53.790
I am going upstairs to change
into my buffet pants!

08:53.790 --> 08:56.120
♪♪

09:00.790 --> 09:02.670
I'm going to be getting some
slice-of-life footage.

09:02.670 --> 09:04.210
Pretend I'm not here...

09:04.210 --> 09:06.290
unless you're giving out
doughnut holes.

09:06.290 --> 09:08.210
Then I would like
to be recognized.

09:08.210 --> 09:09.250
[ Beep ]

09:09.250 --> 09:10.670
Read anything interesting
lately?

09:10.670 --> 09:12.290
Oh, funny
you should ask. Yes.

09:12.290 --> 09:15.670
I just re-read
my old dissertation,

09:15.670 --> 09:17.540
and you can tell,
from even a young age,

09:17.540 --> 09:19.250
I was something special.

09:19.250 --> 09:22.460
[ Chuckles ]

09:22.460 --> 09:24.620
This is what you're wearing?
Jeans?

09:24.620 --> 09:26.250
Yeah.

09:26.250 --> 09:27.710
And if you say
anything more about it,

09:27.710 --> 09:29.500
I'm losing the bra,
and then all hell breaks loose.

09:29.500 --> 09:31.500
We had an agreement.
[ Sighs ]

09:31.500 --> 09:35.120
Greg, can I speak to you
one second in private?

09:35.120 --> 09:37.880
Okay, the appetizers
are done.

09:37.880 --> 09:40.580
If I turn the oven to 600,
will the turkey cook faster?

09:40.580 --> 09:42.620
It doesn't work that way.
Grease would catch fire.

09:42.620 --> 09:43.790
The whole house
would burn down.

09:43.790 --> 09:45.580
I'll be right back.

09:45.580 --> 09:47.580
Anna-Kat,
give us a moment.

09:47.580 --> 09:50.330
Your, uh...sister's
worried about a boy.

09:50.330 --> 09:51.670
How do you know that?

09:51.670 --> 09:53.960
Well, I spent my life
learning how to read people.

09:53.960 --> 09:55.790
It's how I became
successful in business

09:55.790 --> 09:58.380
and how I knew where the warden
hid the flag

09:58.380 --> 09:59.790
when it was
prisoners versus guards

09:59.790 --> 10:01.500
on Spirit Day.

10:01.500 --> 10:03.120
That sounds great.

10:03.120 --> 10:06.080
If I ever go to federal prison,
I'm using you as a reference.

10:06.080 --> 10:08.000
I also see tension between
your grandparents.

10:08.000 --> 10:09.880
Notice they're only
holding hands

10:09.880 --> 10:12.290
by the fingertips.

10:12.290 --> 10:14.040
You're wrong about
that one.

10:14.040 --> 10:16.460
My grandparents have always been
the perfect couple.

10:16.460 --> 10:18.080
Trust me.

10:18.080 --> 10:19.790
People often
put on an act

10:19.790 --> 10:22.710
when they're hiding
their true intentions.

10:25.380 --> 10:26.920
I hear you have
good wine.

10:26.920 --> 10:29.000
Oh, the best!

10:29.000 --> 10:31.170
It's from Thomas Jefferson's
personal collection.

10:31.170 --> 10:32.750
One of only
three bottles left.

10:32.750 --> 10:34.500
[ Chuckles ]

10:34.500 --> 10:38.120
With age
comes perfection.

10:38.120 --> 10:39.540
And wisdom.

10:39.540 --> 10:41.420
Goodbye.

10:41.420 --> 10:44.290
She is so into me!

10:44.290 --> 10:46.460
Whether it's arrogance
or senility,

10:46.460 --> 10:48.250
you wear it well,
my friend.

10:51.620 --> 10:53.750
Katie: I don't like
how he treats you.

10:53.750 --> 10:56.080
Just admit that he is a cold,
withholding jerk,

10:56.080 --> 10:57.540
and I'll get back
on board.

10:57.540 --> 11:00.170
My father is a great man.
If he is so great,

11:00.170 --> 11:02.960
then why hasn't he said anything
about your book?

11:02.960 --> 11:04.880
I'm sure there's
a simple explanation.
Okay.

11:04.880 --> 11:07.170
He doesn't have e-mail,
so I sent him a copy.
Mm-hmm.

11:07.170 --> 11:08.250
The package was too big
for the slot,

11:08.250 --> 11:09.420
so they hid it
behind the ficus.

11:09.420 --> 11:10.750
That's not
a great hiding place.

11:10.750 --> 11:13.040
Someone could have taken it --
an animal, perhaps.

11:13.040 --> 11:14.210
Did you know
that squirrels

11:14.210 --> 11:16.040
can carry up to ten times
their own body weight?

11:16.040 --> 11:17.670
No, I didn't know that.

11:17.670 --> 11:19.620
But what I do know is
I'm gonna go out there

11:19.620 --> 11:21.420
and get plastered
with my tramp mom,

11:21.420 --> 11:23.710
provided she is not abducted
by squirrels.

11:25.080 --> 11:27.290
And then
Jimmy Caan said,

11:27.290 --> 11:30.210
"That was one hell
of a lay over!"

11:30.210 --> 11:32.250
Tell the part where your leg
slipped in the toilet,

11:32.250 --> 11:34.540
and you had to do dinner service
with a blue foot.

11:34.540 --> 11:36.620
No, that's okay.
Let's go talk to Oliver.

11:36.620 --> 11:37.460
He's involved in ballet.

11:37.460 --> 11:39.290
Yes. Let's.

11:42.080 --> 11:44.330
It's so fun
shocking them.

11:44.330 --> 11:46.330
You know, I haven't even
broken the seal yet

11:46.330 --> 11:48.710
about the bi-curious
stories yet.
[ Laughs ]

11:48.710 --> 11:50.040
Look at us.

11:50.040 --> 11:52.170
We're finally
getting along!

11:52.170 --> 11:53.710
Yeah, well...
our tightest bond

11:53.710 --> 11:55.620
has always been
in the criticism of others.

11:55.620 --> 11:58.290
Oh, they are,
without a doubt --

11:58.290 --> 12:01.500
Anna-Kat, Mama is
gonna say words she uses

12:01.500 --> 12:02.750
when she's behind

12:02.750 --> 12:04.380
someone writing a check
at the grocery store.

12:04.380 --> 12:06.460
Could you film
your grandparents instead?

12:08.330 --> 12:10.670
And Harvard's always looking
for male ballerinos.

12:10.670 --> 12:12.170
That's my ticket in.

12:12.170 --> 12:14.880
What complex
machinations.

12:14.880 --> 12:18.250
Oh, wait, wait.
Something's brewing.

12:18.250 --> 12:21.290
"Complexinations!"
Well, hello, new word.

12:21.290 --> 12:24.170
Welcome to the world.
[ Laughs ]

12:24.170 --> 12:26.290
There's actually quite
a few cultural things happening

12:26.290 --> 12:28.420
in this house --
dancing...

12:28.420 --> 12:29.580
writing.

12:29.580 --> 12:30.580
Right.

12:33.790 --> 12:35.580
Oh, enough already.

12:35.580 --> 12:38.040
Thomas, have you read
Greg's damn book?

12:38.040 --> 12:39.580
Uh...

12:39.580 --> 12:40.620
yes.

12:40.620 --> 12:41.880
Thank you.

12:45.790 --> 12:49.120
Anything to add?

12:49.120 --> 12:52.120
[ Camera beeping ]

12:52.120 --> 12:54.580
You're welcome.

12:54.580 --> 12:56.420
Well, great.

12:56.420 --> 12:58.290
I was worried you had
a squirrel problem.

13:03.290 --> 13:04.540
And Greg's father,
that pompous jerk,

13:04.540 --> 13:06.500
just sat there
and didn't say anything.

13:06.500 --> 13:09.120
That's when I snuck out
and gave you guys the 911 text.

13:09.120 --> 13:10.620
Oh, well,
I'm glad you did.

13:10.620 --> 13:12.290
I'm happy to get away
from my family.

13:12.290 --> 13:14.670
I told them I was spotting
and had to lie down.

13:14.670 --> 13:17.460
No one questions you after
you drop the word "spotting."

13:17.460 --> 13:18.670
Hm.

13:18.670 --> 13:20.210
Here's a twist.

13:20.210 --> 13:22.790
I'm getting along with my mom,
but I'm mad at Greg

13:22.790 --> 13:25.330
and super-mad at the way
his father treats him.

13:25.330 --> 13:27.170
So I'm both pissed at
and protective of Greg.

13:27.170 --> 13:29.420
I'm very conflicted.

13:29.420 --> 13:30.880
Do you want to come back with me
for moral support?

13:30.880 --> 13:32.460
[ Inhales sharply ]
Can't. I'm spotting.

13:32.460 --> 13:33.580
Me too.

13:33.580 --> 13:35.460
♪♪

13:35.460 --> 13:36.620
Back from the soup kitchen.

13:36.620 --> 13:37.790
What soup kitchen?

13:37.790 --> 13:39.330
The one in here,
honey.

13:39.330 --> 13:41.880
Okay.
So just nonsense. Right.

13:41.880 --> 13:43.790
Okay! Mom is home!

13:43.790 --> 13:46.380
I would like to invite everybody
to the dinner table.

13:46.380 --> 13:48.960
You're serving starches?
They make me bloat.

13:48.960 --> 13:50.500
I can take a Zantac,
but we'll have to wait for --

13:50.500 --> 13:52.540
Let's just move
to the damn table already!

13:52.540 --> 13:54.830
Come on. Ha!

13:54.830 --> 13:56.040
[ Chuckling ]
All right.

13:59.170 --> 14:01.000
[ Sighs ]
I'm really starting
to like you.

14:01.000 --> 14:02.330
Thanks, Grandma.
Yeah.

14:02.330 --> 14:04.790
Taylor, what in the world
is going on with you?

14:04.790 --> 14:05.880
Dad took my phone.

14:05.880 --> 14:07.080
So...?

14:07.080 --> 14:09.040
Eyo texted
"Happy Thanksgiving."

14:09.040 --> 14:10.670
And then he wrote,
"I love you."

14:10.670 --> 14:12.120
L-U-V?

14:12.120 --> 14:13.500
L-O-V-E.

14:13.500 --> 14:14.830
Damn!

14:17.120 --> 14:19.540
I think Spencer's on to me about
befriending him for his money.

14:19.540 --> 14:20.920
Can you tell
when I'm lying?

14:20.920 --> 14:22.420
I'm not sure.

14:22.420 --> 14:23.710
I really like
your sweater.

14:23.710 --> 14:24.960
Thank you.

14:24.960 --> 14:25.670
Okay, good.
You can't tell.

14:25.670 --> 14:26.920
Very nice.

14:26.920 --> 14:28.000
Now, go get your sister
for dinner.

14:28.000 --> 14:30.290
She's in her room
editing her movie.

14:30.290 --> 14:31.580
Were you going to write back,
"I love you too?"

14:31.580 --> 14:32.540
I guess so.

14:32.540 --> 14:33.750
Well, do you love him?

14:33.750 --> 14:35.000
I don't know.

14:35.000 --> 14:36.460
Then why would you tell him
you do?

14:36.460 --> 14:38.000
It's just texting.

14:38.000 --> 14:39.460
No one expects you
to be fully honest.

14:39.460 --> 14:42.250
Oh, I think I'm gonna
like texting!

14:42.250 --> 14:44.380
Taylor, back when
I was a stewardess,

14:44.380 --> 14:46.250
guys used to throw
the word "love" at me

14:46.250 --> 14:48.920
as freely as they would
throw Quaaludes.

14:48.920 --> 14:52.040
But you have to make sure
the love is real.

14:52.040 --> 14:54.620
Or else you can wake up
in a motel room in Akron

14:54.620 --> 14:56.830
without a ride
to the airport.

14:56.830 --> 14:58.250
I probably still
have 'ludes

14:58.250 --> 15:00.170
caught between
my couch cushions.

15:00.170 --> 15:03.040
You're starting
to grow on me.

15:03.040 --> 15:04.250
Don't worry about
your phone.

15:04.250 --> 15:06.080
Go over to Eyo's now
and talk to him.

15:06.080 --> 15:07.750
You need to do this
face-to-face,

15:07.750 --> 15:09.460
see if it's real.

15:09.460 --> 15:10.380
Thanks, Mom.

15:13.460 --> 15:15.880
I finished my film.
We have to watch it now.

15:15.880 --> 15:17.250
Why can't we watch it
after dinner?

15:17.250 --> 15:18.460
Because after dinner,

15:18.460 --> 15:20.120
you start flashing the lights
on and off,

15:20.120 --> 15:21.670
singing the song
"Closing Time."

15:21.670 --> 15:25.420
♪♪

15:25.420 --> 15:28.120
I can't believe it still works.
We haven't used it in so long.

15:31.210 --> 15:35.670
And, yes, there will be a brief
Q&A after the screening.

15:35.670 --> 15:38.210
[ Beep ]

15:38.210 --> 15:40.500
Thanksgiving means doing
a lot of extra work

15:40.500 --> 15:42.670
for a woman who refuses
to eat my food

15:42.670 --> 15:44.830
and a man who insults
my husband.

15:46.620 --> 15:48.210
Okay, very funny.

15:48.210 --> 15:50.830
Anna-Kat,
make sure you erase that.

15:50.830 --> 15:53.420
Truth is, I've had
all the money in the world,

15:53.420 --> 15:55.540
but Thanksgiving's always been

15:55.540 --> 15:58.330
a bit of a lonely holiday
for me,

15:58.330 --> 15:59.790
because I've --

15:59.790 --> 16:02.620
Well, I never made time
for family.

16:02.620 --> 16:04.580
But I'm thankful
to my new friend

16:04.580 --> 16:06.960
who has...

16:06.960 --> 16:09.540
become my family.

16:09.540 --> 16:11.330
♪♪

16:18.290 --> 16:20.500
Looks like your plan
is working.

16:20.500 --> 16:23.250
Yeah.

16:23.250 --> 16:26.040
[ Dance music plays ]

16:29.420 --> 16:33.250
Thanksgiving!

16:33.250 --> 16:35.540
How's tenure coming?
Oh, I think I'm on-track

16:35.540 --> 16:37.000
to make it in the next
couple of years.

16:37.000 --> 16:40.500
Oh, I made tenure at 28.
Hon, was it 28 or 29?

16:40.500 --> 16:42.460
I jest.
We both know it was 28.

16:42.460 --> 16:43.620
[ Chuckles ]

16:43.620 --> 16:45.170
[ Chuckles ]

16:45.170 --> 16:47.170
Amanda: Honey!
Walk me to the powder room.

16:48.960 --> 16:51.960
[ Laughing ]

16:51.960 --> 16:53.500
[ Snorts ]

16:53.500 --> 16:55.120
[ Clears throat ]

16:59.790 --> 17:02.000
[ Snorts ]

17:02.000 --> 17:05.380
Why are you always such an ass
to Greg?

17:05.380 --> 17:07.960
I'm just giving him something
to live up to.

17:07.960 --> 17:10.830
[ Scoffs ] Oh!
Like you're so great.

17:10.830 --> 17:13.290
We have to turn this off.
Now. Here.

17:13.290 --> 17:14.250
Off!

17:14.250 --> 17:15.460
Um, Grandpa,

17:15.460 --> 17:19.250
that's a toy cellphone filled
with jellybeans.

17:19.250 --> 17:20.960
Say what you will
about Greg.

17:20.960 --> 17:24.380
He hasn't been hiding
a second family

17:24.380 --> 17:27.250
in England
for the last 20 years.

17:27.250 --> 17:28.250
♪♪

17:28.250 --> 17:29.670
[ Chuckles ]

17:29.670 --> 17:31.540
He doesn't even go
to England.

17:31.540 --> 17:33.170
That's not a fair
comparison.

17:34.540 --> 17:35.960
[ Beep ]

17:43.250 --> 17:46.380
♪ Closing time ♪

17:46.380 --> 17:49.250
Wait, you have
a second family?

17:49.250 --> 17:51.250
How long have you known
about this?

17:51.250 --> 17:53.750
Three months ago,
his son called.

17:53.750 --> 17:55.250
Your genius father

17:55.250 --> 17:57.750
left his secret cellphone
in his nightstand.

17:57.750 --> 17:59.580
You have a son?

17:59.580 --> 18:00.460
I have a brother?

18:00.460 --> 18:01.540
Greg.

18:01.540 --> 18:02.620
I'm not talking to you.

18:02.620 --> 18:04.960
No, my other son is
also named Greg.

18:06.040 --> 18:07.250
Greg?!

18:07.250 --> 18:08.460
Why would you
name him Greg?!

18:08.460 --> 18:10.540
You already have a son
named Greg!

18:10.540 --> 18:14.120
So I wouldn't make a mistake
and call you by the wrong name!

18:15.710 --> 18:16.880
Makes perfect sense!

18:16.880 --> 18:19.580
Shut up, just...

18:19.580 --> 18:22.170
shut up.

18:22.170 --> 18:23.710
You know,
every time you visit,

18:23.710 --> 18:26.460
I put Katie and the kids through
hell just to impress you.

18:26.460 --> 18:28.290
We put on this charade.

18:28.290 --> 18:29.420
The funny thing is,
you're the one

18:29.420 --> 18:31.080
who's been putting on
the charade.

18:31.080 --> 18:33.040
But now I see the real you.

18:33.040 --> 18:34.960
Well, Dad...

18:34.960 --> 18:36.500
this is the real me.

18:36.500 --> 18:38.120
We watch TV.

18:38.120 --> 18:39.920
Like, a lot of TV!

18:39.920 --> 18:41.710
We watch all of
"The Bachelors" --

18:41.710 --> 18:44.540
"Bachelorette," "Bachelor Pad,"
and even "Bachelor in Paradise."

18:44.540 --> 18:47.170
My kids love
their cellphones.

18:47.170 --> 18:49.580
Taylor already has arthritis
in her right thumb.

18:49.580 --> 18:51.750
Oh, and you're going to be
so disappointed in this!

18:58.500 --> 19:01.040
Do you know how to make
a whiskey sour?
[ Door opens, closes ]

19:02.500 --> 19:03.420
[ Sighs ]

19:03.420 --> 19:04.710
Eyo and I broke up.

19:04.710 --> 19:05.670
[ Footsteps approach ]

19:05.670 --> 19:06.790
What?

19:06.790 --> 19:10.250
[ Snorting ]

19:10.250 --> 19:11.540
This is our family pet --

19:11.540 --> 19:14.380
a filthy,
garbage-eating pig.

19:14.380 --> 19:16.830
My whole life,
I've looked up to you.

19:16.830 --> 19:19.620
In my eyes,
you couldn't do anything wrong.

19:19.620 --> 19:23.080
In your eyes,
I couldn't do anything right.

19:23.080 --> 19:26.500
Well, it turns out,
I did everything right!

19:26.500 --> 19:28.420
I've got sometimes-great kids

19:28.420 --> 19:31.250
and an
intermittently-great wife!

19:31.250 --> 19:34.000
I had planned on telling you
about Greg, Greg.

19:34.000 --> 19:35.670
I'm not done.

19:35.670 --> 19:37.710
I could give a rat's ass
if you like my book or not.

19:37.710 --> 19:38.920
I like it!

19:38.920 --> 19:40.170
And it's damn good!

19:40.170 --> 19:41.170
Okay.

19:41.170 --> 19:42.920
Okay, you've had
your little say.

19:42.920 --> 19:45.330
All right.
We are getting out of here.

19:45.330 --> 19:47.540
Nobody speaks to me
like this.

19:47.540 --> 19:49.710
Hey, Thomas.

19:49.710 --> 19:51.170
Here's a new word
for you --

19:51.170 --> 19:53.040
"ska-douche!"

19:53.040 --> 19:54.380
That's the sound
the door makes

19:54.380 --> 19:56.000
when you kick a douche
out of the house!

19:58.080 --> 19:59.620
[ Scoffs ]

19:59.620 --> 20:01.710
You will always be
my favorite, Greg!

20:01.710 --> 20:03.460
Because the other one
isn't my son,

20:03.460 --> 20:05.460
and he has a whore
for a mother.

20:08.120 --> 20:10.790
[ Door opens, closes ]

20:10.790 --> 20:14.210
I feel...
like I missed something.

20:14.210 --> 20:16.620
[ Sighs ]
Little bit.

20:16.620 --> 20:18.830
♪♪

20:20.790 --> 20:22.500
You okay?

20:22.500 --> 20:24.080
I'm not gonna lie.
I'm pretty confused right now.

20:24.080 --> 20:27.120
Oh, honey.

20:27.120 --> 20:29.250
The bright side
to this toilet fire is

20:29.250 --> 20:31.290
you're not
an only child anymore.

20:31.290 --> 20:34.080
Yeah, that's true!
Mm-hmm.

20:34.080 --> 20:37.460
How does that
make you feel?

20:37.460 --> 20:39.460
Anna-Kat,
you're not handing that in.

20:39.460 --> 20:41.120
We're just gonna take an "F"
on this one.

20:45.380 --> 20:46.880
Olly, boy,
I want to give you something.

20:46.880 --> 20:48.710
No! I don't want anything
from you.

20:48.710 --> 20:50.710
Having you here is
all I need.

20:50.710 --> 20:54.420
I wasn't giving you
a $50,000 watch, you dummy.

20:54.420 --> 20:56.330
I just want you to take it
and have it cleaned.

20:56.330 --> 20:58.830
Oh.

20:58.830 --> 21:01.500
Appreciate the gesture.

21:01.500 --> 21:03.040
I had my doubts
about you, kid,

21:03.040 --> 21:05.040
but it turned out
I was reading you all wrong.

21:13.120 --> 21:15.790
Sweetheart,
let's head on out.

21:15.790 --> 21:17.790
Yeah, let's go and dig through
those couch cushions.

21:17.790 --> 21:19.500
Ooh, yeah.

21:19.500 --> 21:22.380
♪♪
